=== Footnotes === <div id="MaxNote">† '''Max.''': The maximum combined total when two or more of the same gem are equipped. For example, two [[Agility Up|Agility Up V]] 30 gems will raise a character's [[Agility]] by only 50 points.</div>
=== {{XCFC|sub}} === Since Gem Crafting has been removed in {{XCFC|sublink}}, gems are obtained directly from mining ether deposits, in addition to completing certain [[Bionis' Shoulder Quests]] and opening [[Treasure_Chest#Giants.27_Troves|Giant's Troves]]. Gems of rank II and III can be mined after obtaining the [[Ether Pick]] from [[Carranelle]] in Companions' Cape, and gems of rank IV can be mined after obtaining the [[Reinforced Ether Pick]] from [[Lott]] in Gran Dell.
Gems unobtainable in {{XCFC|sub}} through mining: * [[Bleed Plus]] * [[First Attack Plus]] * [[Back Atk Plus]] * [[Debuff Resist]] ** Reward of ''[[Riddle Faifa This]]'', Rank II - 15% ** Reward of ''[[Lost & Found]]'', Rank V - 50% ** Reward of ''[[The Future Within Our Grasp]]'', Rank V - 50% * [[Unbeatable]] * [[Auto-Heal Up]] * [[Fall Defence]] * [[Terrain Defence]] * [[EXP Up]] ** Unremovable gem of [[Ancestral Artistry]], Rank II - 20% ** Unremovable gem of [[Sage Artistry]], Rank IV - 40% * [[AP Up]] ** Unremovable gem of [[Martial Artistry]], Rank II - 20% ** Unremovable gem of [[Maestro Artistry]], Rank IV - 40% * [[Quick Step]] ** Reward of ''[[Lost & Found]]'', Rank VI - 25%
== {{XC3|-}} == In {{XC3}}, Gems can be [[Gem Crafting|crafted]] at [[Rest Spot (XC3)|Rest Spots]] by [[Riku]] using items picked up across [[Aionios]] or acquired from [[enemy (XC3)|enemies]]. Gems are powerful equipment that can be attached to each character, increasing attack power, recovery power, and other battle-enhancing effects.<ref>[https://twitter.com/XenobladeJP/status/1531170715864510464].</ref>
Only one gem type and rank needs to be crafted as all player characters can equip the same gem. Since each named gem provides a unique effect, crafting a higher ranking gem will lock you out of crafting the weaker, lower rank gems, as you don't need to craft them, saving materials and coins.
==== Gem Crafting ==== {{Main|Gem Crafting}} Each gem type and rank can be crafted by combining specific items and [[Ether Cylinder (XC3)|Ether Cylinders]], or by exchanging [[Nopon Coin (Gold)|Gold Nopon Coins]]. Items can be obtained from blue glow orbs seen from a distance (or detailed icons when up close) strewn across the grounds, vines, and waters of [[Aionios]], enemy drops, [[Supply Drop]]s, [[Container]]s, or purchased from specific [[Nopon Merchant]]s.
For Ether Cylinders, you can store [[Ether]] in them by locating a green glow on the ground, these are known as [[Ether Channel]]s, which are also found strewn across Aionios, or purchase them from specific Nopon Merchants.
Nopon Coins can be obtained via first kill [[Unique Monster (XC3)|Unique Monster]] drops, Supply Drops, Containers, [[Quest (XC3)|Quests]] (including first time only rewards from [[Collectopaedia (XC3)|Collectopaedia Cards]]), or choosing a specific side in [[Skirmish]]es.
In {{XC3FR|sublink}}, Gems can be crafted at Rest Spots once the [[Happy Camper Gear]] has been obtained, as well as at the Ether Furnace in [[Colony 9 (XC1)#Xenoblade Chronicles 3: Future Redeemed|Colony 9]] once it is repaired. Initially when unlocked, only Gems up to rank III can be crafted; completing ''[[The Derelict Ether Furnace]]'' allows Gems up to rank V to be crafted.
Each gem's page lists the specified items needed for each rank.
